
5 July. The congress resolved that John Coburne, assistant conductor of military stores in Canada, be allowed lieutenants pay from 1 March  [255]1 June 1776; that a chaplain be appointed to each regiment in the Continental Army; that immediate steps be taken to procure lead; and that an express be established between New York and Philadelphia to permit General Washington to send daily dispatches to the congress (JCC, 5:522).
